Mar 20 2007 	scalding hot water from both taps	The first impression when you enter the reception lobby is a little alarming as you see giant posters of cabaret dancers. Especially when so many reviews mention the loud noise. And to add to your apprehensions, the lobby seems a little gaudy too.So I asked for a room as far away from the noise as possible and I got it without much ado. My room was nice and clean on the 5th floor, but the water was really hot so I turned on the cold water to neutralize it but to my surprise it was hotter, so I rang the concerned department and they switched off the boiler. I had to wait for an hour for the water to cool down.This exercise had to be done very morning and after a certain while I started feeling like boiled meat. It was certainly cumbersome to wait for the right temperature water to come so you could take a shower so inevitably risks had to be taken.Otherwise the staff was very polite and hospitable. The breakfast was very ordinary and it was a formality to have it, before you went out.My overall experience was OK!	
Feb 19 2007 	Do not stay here if you have any option unless you are an insomniac	I stayed at the hotel whilst in Dubai on business and unfortunately would have to say that the whole experience of my first visit to Dubai was overshadowed by the deafening noise from the disco which went on until the early hours of the morning on all four nights that I stayed at the hotel. Despite of the fact that my colleague and I asked to be moved after the first night, and were relocated to the 5th floor, the noise was still overwhelming. As there are many good alternative hotels available in Dubai, if a little expensive in the main, there really is no need to suffer the terrible noise at the Orchid. Avoid at all costs.	
