Dec 1 2006 	Orchid - Basic not Beautiful	I picked the Orchid because it was close to the Al Bustan where I was attending a conference - but considerably cheaper! The rooms were basic but clean - which was all I was looking for. Don't expect a bell boy to assist you - there was one.....sometimes! Several night clubs on 1st floor - which is not unusual for 3 star hotels in Dubai. Due to my attending social functions which ended late, I can't comment on the noise from the clubs as they had finished by the time I returned to the hotel. The particular thing I enjoyed about this hotel is that they serve food until 4.30am in a small restaurant in the lobby - where there is a great mix of people. I particularly recommend the spicy beef and fried rice.....tasted great in the early hours - and sent me to bed satisfied!I wouldn't recommend this hotel if you are trying to impress that special person in your life - but for the single business traveler who doesn't plan to spend too much time in it - it's fine and good value by the ever increasing Dubai price standards.I would return......but only for the spicy beef!	
Nov 23 2006	Value for money	Good location only 10 minutes walk from Bur Dubai, the souks and creek. Always a taxi passing the hotel or nearby main road every minute for longer trips away.The rooms are very basic, but clean. Just don't go on the balcony - we had to ask for a key to be allowed access to ours and then had to wade through several inches of sand and dust. Don't expect a romantic balcony experience here!The nightclubs are loud, going on until 2am each night, but thats part of the Dubai experience! The Filipino one was always good for a nightcap, the clientel was almost exclusively Filipino and the occasional Arab in national dress. Filipino bands playing covers of classic rock and pop tunes, the customers seemed very pleased to see a couple of westerners and made us feel at home. The downstairs club featured a Russian girl/boy duet called Tease, playing a mixture of Western and Russian pop covers, who were so awful we spent hours watching them each night! Try to imagine Arnold Schwarzenegger singing &quot;Mambo Number Five&quot; and you'll get the idea! Despite the unintentionally hilarious act, this club rarely had more than 10 people in it. The barlady was also very aggressive when I dared take a photograph of my friend in there, although I since learnt that using cameras in Middle East nightclubs is a big no-no, presumably the many Arabs getting sloshed on Budweiser didn't want their photos posting on the web. We also made the mistake of assuming the many Russian girls working there as dancers/singers did extra work in the bedrooms - wrong! They were insulted to say the least.The pool area was a joke, just about big enough to call it a bathtub (and unheated at that). The area around it, surrounded by air-con vents and kitchen extractor outlets, was just about big enough to accommodate 10 fat Russians - the clientel was very E European and most of these were hideous, milk-white, gold toothed, overweight, loud men who spent all day/night drinking cheap liquor by the pool. Atmospheric in a way though.Service was excellent, bar breakfast. Where at 10am the waiters would wait by your table and snatch your plates/cups as soon as they became empty. Arrive at 1001 for breakfast and there wouldn't be a crumb left. The breakfast wasn't too appetising either - lamb curry at 9 in the morning ? No thanks.Good for young travellers on a budget and who won't be going to bed until 2am, otherwise avoid.	
Nov 22 2006 	Horrible	My heart sank as we pulled up. Smell of smoke in the room and damp. No hot water, loud music all night.I booked it through the virgin website, looking for a fairly cheap long weekend.After two nights (I'm sure it was full of prostitutes at night) we ran screaming and blew all our cash on the Jumeriah Beach Hotel.	
Mar 2 2006	Won't Rush Back	A group of five of us stayed at the Orchid for 3 nights at the end of February 06. We had all been to a wedding in India and were looking for a few days to chill before returning home. We were a mixed group of males and females and of ages. We found the staff to be pleasant and helpful. The hotel has 3 nightclubs all based on the First Floor and they are all open till the early hours of the morning. We had rooms on both the 4 and 5 floors and 4 of the party required ear plugs to ensure a good night sleep.The breakfast buffy is very basic and is served in Cindy's Phillipino Night Club. Interesting having breakfust under ultra violet lights and sitting with people in their night clothes.All things considered if you are looking for a hotel close to the airport for 1 or 2 nights then this hotel is okay. However we are sure that if you search the web you will find nicer and more reasonably priced hotels. Our rooms cost approx £90/night including breakfast.We intend to return to Dubai but will look for a better hotel next time.	
